```plantuml
@startuml
title PB-749 UC4 - Update a Banner on System Management

actor "System Management" as SM
participant "Core Next" as CN
database "Next Database" as DB
participant "Core Bradesco" as CB

box "Next Platform" #LightGray
    participant CN
    database DB
end box

note over CN: Abstract:\nThis use case will be responsible to update an existing banner on Next.\nThis endpoint is not responsible for deleting a record. To do this, it\nmust use the use case 5 - Delete a Banner on System Management.\nHowever, in this use case, SM may enable or disable Banner.

SM -> CN: 1 PUT /v1/notification/banner/{bannerID}
note right of SM: System Management will call this new endpoint\npassing all the fields necessary to update an\nexisting Banner. The fields are:\n1. BANNER_ID\n2. BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE_ID\n3. TEMPLATE_HEADER\n4. TEMPLATE_BODY\n5. ENABLE_IND

activate CN
CN -> DB: 2 check if this Banner exists on BANNER table
note right of CN: Core Next will check if this Banner exists on BANNER table
activate DB
DB --> CN: 3 response
deactivate DB

alt if the Banner exists
    CN -> DB: 4 check if exists an enabled Banner associated with that BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE received on requisition on BANNER table
    activate DB
    note right of CN: <b>Note to developers</b>\nCore Next will check if exists any Banner linked to a BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE on BANNER\ntable. We can only have one enabled Banner linked to a BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE. For this\nrule, we should disregard the records that are with DELETE_FLG enabled and the Card itself.
    DB --> CN: 5 response
    deactivate DB

    alt if exists an enabled Banner associated with that BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE
        note right of CN: If exists any Banner linked to a BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE passed by App,\nwe will throw back an error to App side.
        CN --> SM: 6 error
        note right of SM: HTTP code: 422 #Pink
    else if don't exists an enabled Banner associated with that BUSINESS_EVENT_TYPE
        note right of CN: If the defensive checks pass, then we will update the register on BANNER table.
        CN -> DB: 7 update the register on BANNER table
        activate DB
        DB --> CN: 8 success
        deactivate DB
        CN --> SM: 9 success
        note right of SM: HTTP code: 200 #LightBlue
    end
else if the Banner don't exists
    CN --> SM: 10 error
    note right of SM: If the Banner don't exists on\nBANNER table, then we will\nthrow back an error to SM.\nHTTP code: 404 #Pink
end

deactivate CN
@enduml
```